13

architectural design of a mobile application enables context-awareness, particularly with respect to different system contexts. Several model-driven development frameworks do in fact support the generation of native program code; however, they follow a rich-client architecture (Applause [Beh10] [05]) or a client-server architecture (Modagile [08]). Thus, they are either only offline-capable or only online-capable.

To sum up, we face the challenge of context-awareness and propose a model-driven

1.34

